task.summary: Trojan, Client/Server round-up, Command reimplementation completed working on the trojan shell and the command shell specificly, fixed some major bugs with the Server/Client communication between PiServer and the User. This is the first partly working prototype, the connection process and the command functionality work, although only tested on one computer

First finished, but slim version Mainly did some tweeking with the display of received trojans replies and adjusted the scriptshell, so that scripts will also work with the new trojan management system. Next step is testing the trojan on a global ip range

Command Fix Fixed a bug, where only one command could be successfully issued per session due to the end sequence getting stuck in the receive_buffer of the user side client, thus always breaking the receive loop
